text.tspan: Explore the effect of demographics upon policing in your area
Help create the first ever Europe-wide map of law enforcement,
created by the people and for the people
We hope that users will find our tooling helpful in gaining insight into
where, when & how the police in their precinct operate, plus exactly
who (in non-identifying demographic terms) policing affects the most.
To achieve this, we may vet the uploaded data (manual or automatic)
as well as taking measures to maintain trust in the data of our users:
- initial app release is to a closed group of specially selected people.
- after some time a user may invite a limited number of others.
- upon generally availability each user will be evaluated to quantify
how authentic they appear, based on factors like 'are they logged in'
and 'do we have a confirmed email address to contact them with', etc.
CREATE AN ACCOUNT OR LOG IN TO ACCESS
TAP HERE TO COPY YOUR URL
In addition to the recording functionality, the BLUE BOOK app shall also
provide visualisation of data uploaded either by the user themselves,
or uploaded by other users who have the appropriate visibility setting.
Our primary concern when it comes to data collection is to ensure that
it meets the high standards we require for accuracy & authenticity.
Long term, we aim to corroborate each user upload against other data.
